Biafra Nations League (BnL) on Monday sent out a stern warning to the Federal government over the long detention of Nnamdi Kanu, the incarcerated leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, (IPOB)and other Igbos in various prisons and custody across the country. According to the deputy leader of the group, Ebuta Takon, they will come up with a strategy that will result to a huge problem for the Nigerian government. Takon disclosed this while speaking to reporters in Ikom, Cross River State, reacting to the April 14 adjournment of the trial of Nnamdi Kanu, the leader of Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB). Buhari Demands Return Of More Nigeria’s Artefacts From Abroad 2023: South-South Lawmakers Endorse Yahaya Bello For President “Justice delayed is justice denied. They’re delaying because they’re in control of every court. Keeping our people in detention to suffer and frustrate them, we will not allow that. “We’ll come up with a strategy that will be a big problem to them and they wouldn’t know how to go about it,” he said.